An Act relative to growing resources to optimize the utilization of group therapeutic care.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 13 of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the following
2 section:-
3 Section 110. (a) There shall be a board of certification of group therapeutic specialists,
4 called the board in this section. The board shall consist of 12 members who shall be residents of
5 the commonwealth as follows: the commissioner of the department of public health or a
6 designee, who shall serve as chair of the board; the commissioner of the department of mental
7 health or a designee; eight persons appointed by the governor; one person appointed by the
8 speaker of the house of representatives; and one person appointed by the president of the senate.
9 Of the appointed members of the board, 1 shall be a certified group therapeutic specialist,
10 provided that such person initially appointed to the board shall be eligible for board certification
11 as a group therapeutic specialist and shall obtain such certification within a time frame specified
12 in regulations adopted by the board; 1 shall represent an organization that provides group
